{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1772200773,"nonce":"vA8Yf/caKbOf9OE1GTYgGD9ZJyo=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87ufQ8a","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/305","origin":"github"},"title":"Point non-Claude framework adapters to existing workflow skills","message":"## Problem\n\nThe workspace has a collection of workflow skills (review-issue, plan-task, review-pr, brainstorm, research, audit-workspace, audit-project, gather-project-knowledge) defined in `.claude/skills/*/SKILL.md`. These skills are plain markdown with numbered steps, `gh` CLI commands, and structured output templates — nothing in the content is Claude Code-specific.\n\nHowever, other framework instruction files (Gemini CLI, Copilot, generic onboarding) don't reference these skills, so agents using those frameworks can't discover or use them.\n\n## Proposed Solution\n\nAdd a short section to each non-Claude framework adapter pointing agents to `.claude/skills/` as a read-only reference:\n\n- `.agent/instructions/gemini-cli.instructions.md`\n- `.github/copilot-instructions.md`\n- `.agent/AGENT_ONBOARDING.md`\n\nSomething like:\n\n\u003e **Workflow skills**: Reusable workflow procedures are documented in `.claude/skills/*/SKILL.md`. When asked to review an issue, plan a task, review a PR, brainstorm, or run research, read the corresponding SKILL.md and follow its steps.\n\n## Why not move skills to a framework-neutral location?\n\nPer Principle 10 (\"Primary framework first, portability where free\"), the skills should stay where Claude Code discovers them natively. Moving them to `.agent/skills/` would add indirection for the primary framework to benefit hypothetical secondary use. Pointing other frameworks at the existing location is the minimal change.\n\n## Scope\n\n1. Add a \"Workflow skills\" section to each non-Claude adapter file (3 files)\n2. Optionally list the available skills by name so agents don't need to glob the directory\n\n## Constraints\n\n- Don't move or restructure `.claude/skills/` — this is about discovery, not reorganization\n- Keep the additions minimal (2-4 lines per file)","files":null}]}